"{\"abstract\":\"Graph cuts have proven useful for image segmentation and for volumetric reconstruction in multiple view stereo. However, solutions are biased: the cost function tends to favour either a short boundary (in 2D) or a boundary with a small area (in 3D). This bias can be avoided by instead minimising the cut ratio, which normalises the cost by a measure of the boundary size. This paper uses ideas from discrete differential geometry to develop a linear programming formulation for finding a minimum ratio cut in arbitrary dimension, which allows constraints on the solution to be specified in a natural manner, and which admits an efficient and globally optimal solution. Results are shown for 2D segmentation and for 3D volumetric reconstruction.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"2537623\",\"name\":\"F. Nicolls\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2537623\"},{\"authorId\":\"143635540\",\"name\":\"P. Torr\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/143635540\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"2900886\",\"name\":\"Yansheng Ming\"},{\"authorId\":\"40124570\",\"name\":\"Hongdong Li\"},{\"authorId\":\"33913193\",\"name\":\"Xuming He\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1109/TIP.2014.2372636\",\"intent\":[\"background\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"0b9cd1fe86a01567d0182105c8ae27e6574bd3b3\",\"title\":\"Winding Number Constrained Contour Detection\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/0b9cd1fe86a01567d0182105c8ae27e6574bd3b3\",\"venue\":\"IEEE Transactions on Image Processing\",\"year\":2015},{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"1750819\",\"name\":\"L. Grady\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1201/B12281-5\",\"intent\":[],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"2f2123cdb2a31624d1aedeb08fc2c026021be31e\",\"title\":\"Targeted Image Segmentation Using Graph Methods\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/2f2123cdb2a31624d1aedeb08fc2c026021be31e\",\"venue\":\"\",\"year\":2017},{\"a